# 2. Types of Proofs You Actually Use

## Direct Proof

| Template |
|---|
| Assume hypotheses |
| Apply definitions + known results |
| Derive conclusion |

**Used for:** convexity, PSD arguments, norm inequalities.

---

## Proof by Contrapositive

| Form |
|---|
| Prove \( \neg Q \Rightarrow \neg P \) instead of \( P\Rightarrow Q \) |

**Used for:** uniqueness, identifiability, rank arguments.

---

## Proof by Contradiction

| Form |
|---|
| Assume negation of claim |
| Derive impossibility |

**Used for:** non-existence, impossibility results, lower bounds.

---

# 3. Equality, Inequality, and Bounding Arguments

## Equality Proofs

| Pattern | Use |
|---|---|
| Expand both sides | Algebraic identities |
| Reduce to zero | Norms, quadratic forms |
| Invariant argument | Basis changes, similarity |

---

## Inequality Proofs (High-Frequency)

| Tool | When It Appears |
|---|---|
| Cauchy–Schwarz | Inner products |
| Jensen | Convex expectations |
| Triangle inequality | Error decomposition |
| PSD ordering | Matrix bounds |

**Failure mode:** applying inequality without checking assumptions (convexity, integrability).

