# 4. Existence, Uniqueness, and Identifiability

## Existence

| Method | Typical Use |
|---|---|
| Explicit construction | Minimizers, estimators |
| Compactness + continuity | Existence of optima |
| Probabilistic existence | Random constructions |

---

## Uniqueness

| Template |
|---|
| Assume two solutions |
| Show difference = 0 |

**ML relevance:** uniqueness of minimizers, representations, decompositions.

---

## Identifiability

| Pattern |
|---|
| Show distinct parameters ⇒ distinct distributions / models |

---

