# 8. Linear Algebra Proof Patterns (Used Everywhere)

## Orthogonality Arguments

| Pattern |
|---|
| Decompose into orthogonal components |
| Apply Pythagoras |
| Minimize norm via projection |

---

## Spectral Arguments

| Pattern |
|---|
| Diagonalize (or SVD) |
| Reduce matrix claim to scalar claim |
| Lift back to matrix |

---

## Rank Arguments

| Pattern |
|---|
| Count dimensions |
| Use rank–nullity |
| Derive impossibility |

---

# 9. Proof Hygiene (What Reviewers Expect)

## Structural Discipline

| Rule | Why |
|---|---|
| State assumptions | Prevent hidden constraints |
| Name the theorem | Justify step |
| Separate lemmas | Reduce cognitive load |
| Quantify explicitly | Avoid ambiguity |
| Close the loop | State conclusion |

---

## Common Failure Modes in ML Papers

| Mistake | Why It Fails |
|---|---|
| Implicit uniformity | Breaks limits |
| Unchecked convexity | Invalid Jensen |
| Dimension mismatch | Silent linear algebra error |
| Ignoring null sets | Invalid probability claim |

